Allstate Says Catastrophes Cost Insurer $735 Million in August

-- B y   N o a h   B u h a y a r
-- 
2011-09-15T12:14:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/allstate-says-catastrophes-cost-insurer-735-million-in-august.html
Allstate Corp. (ALL) , the largest
publicly traded U.S. home and auto insurer, had pretax losses of
$735 million last month from natural disasters, including
Hurricane Irene.  Irene, the first hurricane to strike the U.S. since 2008,
cost the insurer about $500 million pretax, Northbrook,
Illinois-based Allstate said today in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Noah Buhayar in New York at 
 nbuhayar@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  